The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Day II highlights
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Day II highlights
                      
	The 314-run partnership between Gautam Gambhir and Rahul Dravid is now Indias best vs England for the second wicket. The previous best was 192 by Farokh Engineer and Ajit Wadekar at Brabourne in 1972-93.         
	 The partnership between Gambhir and Dravid is the third double century partnership for any wicket on this ground and Dravid has been involved in two of them.         
	 The partnership between Gambhir and Dravid is the best for any wicket on this ground. The previous best was 231 for the first wicket by New Zealands M. Richardson and L. Vincent in 2003-04.         
	 The partnership between Gambhir and Dravid is now the second best for any wicket against England. The best remains 316 for the 3rd wkt by GR Viswanath amp; Yashpal Sharma at Chepauk 1981-82.         
	 Dravid has now been involved in 11 double century stands. Among Indians only Tendulkar (14) has more.         
	 Gambhir has now been involved in four double century stands in Test cricket.         
	 This was the second double century stand for the second wicket between Gambhir and Dravid. They had put on 259 for the second wicket vs Bangladesh at Chittagong in 2004-05.         
	 Rahul Dravid recorded his 26th Test hundred. It was his 10th at home. It was also Dravids fourth century vs England, but his first vs England on Indian soil.         
	 Dravids previous highest score vs England at home was 95 at Mohali in 2005-06.         
	 On 142 Gambhir became the seventh player and fourth Indian to score 1000 runs in the calendar year 2008.         
	 Gambhir became the 10th player to score 1000 runs in both Tests and ODIs in a calendar year. Tendulkar (1997) and Ganguly (2007) are the other Indians to score 1000 runs in a year in Tests and ODIs.         
	 Four Indian batsmen have scored 1000 runs in the year 2008  the most by Indian batsmen in a single year. The previous best was three by Gavaskar, Vengsarkar and Viswanath in the year 1979.         
	 Gambhir (179) now has the highest individual score on this ground.           MOHANDAS MENON                                                                                                                      
